<subSubSection id="C3012AA0FA07FFBFFF71FC79FDF2903D" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA4792BFA07FFBFFF71FC79FE8A9695" blockId="38.[151,450,871,930]" box="[151,330,906,930]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
(
<figureCitation id="132065AEFA07FFBFFF79FC79FE829695" box="[159,322,906,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–154" captionStartId="37.[151,263,1810,1833]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,206,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-79@37.[151,1436,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 143–154. Thrips species. T. minutissimus, female 143–148: (143) Head &amp; pronotum; (144) Antenna, right; (145) Metascutum; (146) Tergite VI &amp; pleurotergite, right side; (147) Tergites VIII–X; (148) Sternite VII, sculpture omitted. T. nigropilosus, female 149–152: (149) Head &amp; pronotum; (150) Antenna, right; (151) Metascutum; (152) Tergites II–III, right side. T. nigropilosus, male 153–154: (153) Tergites VII–IX; (154) Sternite VI." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Figs. 149–154</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4792BFA07FFBFFF71FC21FDF2903D" blockId="38.[151,1436,978,1290]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
This species is almost cosmopolitan and is found throughout 
<collectingCountry id="F30C39BBFA07FFBFFC84FC20FC6596DD" box="[866,933,979,1002]" name="Japan" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Japan</collectingCountry>
. It is polyphagous but especially breeds on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B02A8FA07FFBFFF71FC05FED59139" box="[151,277,1014,1038]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B02A8FA07FFBFFE30FC04FDFB9139" box="[470,571,1014,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tabaci">
<emphasis id="B96FA539FA07FFBFFE30FC04FDFB9139" box="[470,571,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">T. tabaci</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B02A8FA07FFBFFD9FFC04FD279139" box="[633,743,1015,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urticae">
<emphasis id="B96FA539FA07FFBFFD9FFC04FD279139" box="[633,743,1015,1038]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">T. urticae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the following character states: body generally yellowish brown or brownish yellow with brown markings, 7-segmented antenna (
<figureCitation id="132065AEFA07FFBFFC39FBE9FB839105" box="[991,1091,1050,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–154" captionStartId="37.[151,263,1810,1833]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,206,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-79@37.[151,1436,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 143–154. Thrips species. T. minutissimus, female 143–148: (143) Head &amp; pronotum; (144) Antenna, right; (145) Metascutum; (146) Tergite VI &amp; pleurotergite, right side; (147) Tergites VIII–X; (148) Sternite VII, sculpture omitted. T. nigropilosus, female 149–152: (149) Head &amp; pronotum; (150) Antenna, right; (151) Metascutum; (152) Tergites II–III, right side. T. nigropilosus, male 153–154: (153) Tergites VII–IX; (154) Sternite VI." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 150</figureCitation>
), metascutum (
<figureCitation id="132065AEFA07FFBFFB13FBE9FA979105" box="[1269,1367,1050,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–154" captionStartId="37.[151,263,1810,1833]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,206,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-79@37.[151,1436,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 143–154. Thrips species. T. minutissimus, female 143–148: (143) Head &amp; pronotum; (144) Antenna, right; (145) Metascutum; (146) Tergite VI &amp; pleurotergite, right side; (147) Tergites VIII–X; (148) Sternite VII, sculpture omitted. T. nigropilosus, female 149–152: (149) Head &amp; pronotum; (150) Antenna, right; (151) Metascutum; (152) Tergites II–III, right side. T. nigropilosus, male 153–154: (153) Tergites VII–IX; (154) Sternite VI." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 151</figureCitation>
) with reticulation medially and abdominal tergite VIII with complete posteromarginal comb in female, tergite IX with a pair of CPS, sternites and pleurotergites without discal setae. However, it can be distinguished easily from the other members of this genus by a combination of the following character states: compound eyes with five pigmented ommatidia ventrally (
<figureCitation id="132065AEFA07FFBFFE68FB59FE3391F5" box="[398,499,1194,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–154" captionStartId="37.[151,263,1810,1833]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,206,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-79@37.[151,1436,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 143–154. Thrips species. T. minutissimus, female 143–148: (143) Head &amp; pronotum; (144) Antenna, right; (145) Metascutum; (146) Tergite VI &amp; pleurotergite, right side; (147) Tergites VIII–X; (148) Sternite VII, sculpture omitted. T. nigropilosus, female 149–152: (149) Head &amp; pronotum; (150) Antenna, right; (151) Metascutum; (152) Tergites II–III, right side. T. nigropilosus, male 153–154: (153) Tergites VII–IX; (154) Sternite VI." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 149</figureCitation>
), female often (male always) micropterous, fore wing uniformly pale but usually with small weak shaded area subbasally when macropterous, and abdominal tergites with sculpture lines medially and S1 setae longer (
<figureCitation id="132065AEFA07FFBFFE67FB01FDE6903D" box="[385,550,1266,1290]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–154" captionStartId="37.[151,263,1810,1833]" captionTargetBox="[163,1424,206,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-79@37.[151,1436,193,1789]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 143–154. Thrips species. T. minutissimus, female 143–148: (143) Head &amp; pronotum; (144) Antenna, right; (145) Metascutum; (146) Tergite VI &amp; pleurotergite, right side; (147) Tergites VIII–X; (148) Sternite VII, sculpture omitted. T. nigropilosus, female 149–152: (149) Head &amp; pronotum; (150) Antenna, right; (151) Metascutum; (152) Tergites II–III, right side. T. nigropilosus, male 153–154: (153) Tergites VII–IX; (154) Sternite VI." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Figs. 152, 153</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
